# Walkthrough - Unify Currency Presentation

I have unified the presentation of monetary values across the application. Now, positive currency values appear in **Green** and negative currency values appear in **Red**, while non-currency counts remain **Black**.

## Changes

### Frontend
- **[App.css](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/Facturas/frontend/src/App.css)**:
    - Added utility classes `.text-currency-positive` (Green) and `.text-currency-negative` (Red).
- **[StatCard.tsx](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/Facturas/frontend/src/components/molecules/StatCard/StatCard.tsx)**:
    - Updated logic to **only** apply color when the value contains a currency symbol (`$`).
    - Counts and other numbers remain neutral (Black).
- **[App.tsx](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/Facturas/frontend/src/App.tsx)**:
    - Updated "Import Preview" and "Report Results" tables to apply these classes to monetary columns.

